Doc,<br><br>
For once we totally agree on something.<br><br>
&quot;The lowest common demoninator seems to seek its own and spread like the Ebola Virus&quot;<br><br>
A self portrait I presume.  I have struggled to not see you as others do.  The subtleties in your post begin to paint a picture which makes me uncomfortable.  You are not what you want us to believe.<br><br>
I for one am still an active member of this society that keeps the hounds at the gate.  Watch that you do not loosen the roots that hold you this great nation.  It would be only too easy to let a strong wind blow you away.<br><br>
We benefit from the diversity of opinion.  You detest the pack mentality and yet you ask for your own pack.  Do not confuse pack mentality with brotherhood and camaraderie.  It takes a certain kinship to bind men or as we say warriors together.  You must understand this because you plead for it daily.  It appears it is something we have and you desparately seek.<br><br>
Never fear about the death of this site.  We want it as much as you apparently do.  Rather need.<br><br>
By the way Doc the highest medal this old soldier was awarded was a peace time medal.  Guess what that might be.  I didn't not have to kill or molest anyone to get it.  It still required teamwork form members of all forces which were on my team at the time.<br><br>
Doc if you want pack mentality you should study the ROCs.  I lived in their compound.  Ruthless, final, unchallenged by charlie.  Maintained our SAR sites.  A Hyena Pack that was all you think a pack might be.  Disciplined beyond belief. You are clueless about the real bad boys in NAM.  They weren't US soldiers.<br><br>
I for one will cease to attempt respect for anyone who shows the disdain for the American fighting man.  Anyone who supports such behavior is contemtible.<br><br>
This is my feeling and if anyone disagrees, I frankly don't give a damn.<br><br>
A member of the pack with no regrets.
